Who's leading your Parade?
Every day you are bombarded by messages. The messages are communicated
from the leaders of fashion, entertainment, politics, and finance (to
name a few). They cleverly communicate message about the way you should
think, feel, behave, and look. They are successful at getting the masses
to follow them. They are leading the parade and getting everyone to buy
into their products, philosophy, style, and culture. Think that you are
not impacted by these leaders? Think again. They influence your
decisions regarding your diet, health, leisure time, travel, wardrobe,
and spending. In fact, they are leading the entire culture into a new
way of thinking about life style, family, priorities, and norms. It is
hard not to get caught up in their parade! It is fun, beautiful,
comfortable, and exciting. It is easier to be swept along with the
majority and give in to their thinking and standards.
Of course, that may be what is easy, but it certainly is not what is
best. The only one that you should be following is Jesus Christ. Have a
question about something the world is telling you to do, be, or
participate in? Look to Jesus. Read the Word. Ask Him for the answer in
pray and meditation. Don't get swept away by the world's overwhelming
tidal wave of influence. Stop and ask yourself who is leading your
parade. Are you following the parade of the world and in the process
compromising your integrity and standards? If so, make a decision today
to step away from the crowd and surrender your life to Jesus Christ.
When He is your leader, the choices in your life are no longer
meaningless reactions to the world around you, but rather, are
purposeful and powerful decision that will result in the blessings that
only He can provide.
My sheep listen to my voice; I know them, and they follow me. John
10:27  --The Daily Journey

