Hope Is Eternal
Hope is a word we hear almost every day by people wishing the best
outcome to be.
It's &quot;hope for the best&quot; with sheer positive thinking for the future
they can't even see.
But the very word &quot;hope&quot; has different meaning for the Christian who
lives by His call.
For that hope is the anchor of their very own lives as they trust Him as
their one and all.
Hope is the promises of God for His children regardless of the outcomes
of life.
For hope holds the soul in the palm of His hand through heartache &amp;
seasons of strife.
That hope is not passing...like a fleeting emotion when it is fixed on
the glory of the King.
For it's hope that reveals God's everlasting beauty and will give you a
new song to sing.
This hope for the believer is not earthly hope but it's eternal, in a
world yet unseen.
It is permanent and solid...exceeding all human reason and surpassing
our mere, mortal dreams.
This hope is the surety and the seed of eternity planted deep in the
heart's fertile sod.
For hope is a person and His name is Jesus sitting high at the right
hand of God.
--Sheila Gosney

